/some_unknown_person tells you &quot;do you have CS port&quot;<br>
I know what's coming but Im a glutton for punishment I guess<br>
/tell some_unknown_person &quot;Yes&quot;<br>
/some_unknown_person tells you &quot;Would you TP me to CS?&quot;<br>
/who some_unknown_person<br>
Unknown_person is now known as Level_47_wizard<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;Sorry I'm lfg and you should know how much it sux to receive a port tell&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;You can bind here and gate back&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;you gotta be kidding, you gotta have the key to port into CS&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;I have the key&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;then port yourself&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;I don't have the spell, where do you get it?&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;they sell it in SS and its dropped&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;I'm KOS in SS&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;then get someone to buy it for you, that's what i did, or go auction for it&quot;<br>
silence<br>
I zone back into KC and do another /shout LFG <br>
You have gotten better at Looking for Group! (679210587)<br>
Your faction standing with family has gotten worse.<br>
Your faction standing with people in zone has gotten worse.<br>
I commence talking to friends and relate the exchange through tell to another person but before i could do that I get a /tell again from Level_47_wizard<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;please port me&quot;<br>
So my /tell to my friend relating the exchange goes to him instead<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;???, your mad about a port request?&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;you know how much port requests suck from unknowns&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;but I'm in a good mood, meet me at the tunnel and I'll port you&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;just gate to spires&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;ok now you suck&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;??? wrong tell again?&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;nope that was for you, you ask me for a favor, you didn't offer money, you won't come to me instead demand I come to you, you suck&quot;<br>
/Level_47_wizard tells you &quot;/rude&quot;<br>
/tell Level_47_wizard &quot;lol /ignore&quot;<br>
<br>
Seriously though I was feeling guilty about it for a while, must suck to not have the spell yet, but I ported myself into CS to see if the hunting was good, but it was overcamped, 22 people in zone, bah, and sure enough Level_47_wizard has found a port there.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uevaldamriveneficus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evaldamri Veneficus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 11:28:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rudest port request you've ever received</span><hr size=1> Simple rules to live by with porting.<br>
<br>
1. If you're in the guild I'll port you - no questions asked as long as I'm not in a group.   If I'm just doing something solo for me which is a camp I can leave and come back to or working on trade skills I'll port you no prob.<br>
<br>
2. I don't generally charge for ports but if someone offers me money I'll take it.  I won't drop anything no matter how mundane I may be doing for a port but I will probably trans you.<br>
<br>
3.  Translocates - no regeant no ride unless you're in my guild.<br>
<br>
Guess that about sums it up.   If it's a guildie in need I'll go out of my way to help.   If it's random chumly I'll help if it's convenient - such as I'm already heading there anyway or just bumming around.   If someone gets lippy or rude then go bugger yourself.  I usually will help somene in a CR situation.<br>
<br>
The only other caviot is - if money is involved or an item then you pay before you ride.  End of discussion.<br>
